## HUD.ai Overview
HUD.ai is an AI agent evaluation and RL (Reinforcement Learning) environment platform that turns test results into training data for fine-tuning models. It specializes in RFT (Reinforcement Fine-Tuning) to boost agent performance on custom tasks using eval trajectories and rewards. [docs.hud](https://docs.hud.ai/reference/cli/rft)

## Core Functionality
- **RFT Training**: Run via CLI (`hud rft run tasks.json`) on JSONL tasks from HUD evals; integrates with OpenAI/Tinker backends for 2x gains (e.g., 13% success on hard benchmarks). [docs.hud](https://docs.hud.ai/reference/cli/rft)
- **Environments**: Isolated setups for agent testing, supporting remote MCP configs but no vision yet. [hud](https://www.hud.ai/resources/platforms-agent-evals-rl-training-data)
- **Pricing**: $0.25+/env hour; free credits available. [docs.hud](https://docs.hud.ai/reference/cli/rft)

